
[1]acerb

   ACERB', a. [L. acerbus; G. herbe, harsh, sour, tart, bitter, rough,
   whence herbst autumn, herbstzeit, harvest time. See Harvest.]

   Sour, bitter, and harsh to the taste; sour, with astringency or
   roughness; a quality of unripe fruits.
